As CS Lewis is quoted as saying in William Nicholson’s play Shadowlands, “we read to know we are not alone”. As the world came to a standstill and entire countries locked down, you may have turned to books for solace and inspiration, or just for a dose of escapism. We would like to hear which new books you rated the most in this year of change and readjustment. Tell us all about your favourite books published in 2020. You can get in touch by filling in the form below. Your responses are secure as the form is encrypted and only the Guardian has access to your contributions. One of our journalists will be in contact before we publish, so please do leave contact details. If you’re having trouble using the form, click here. Read terms of service here.